I took the time this weekend to get the feature implemented in Geary. So far Geary recognizes the Exchange accounts in GOA, but I'm stuck at setting the IMAP/SMTP addresses. I would like to propose that gnome-online-accounts sets its IMAP/SMTP fields for Exchange accounts, to the same URL as the Exchange accounts (indeed the same Exchange server also supports IMAP/SMTP). I dread having to change the GLib/C GOA codebase, working on the Geary Vala code is so much more accessible :sweat_smile:
Without this change, Geary activates the account, but then it gets stuck a bit later since the IMAP/SMTP URLs are not set. I modified `Accounts.Manager.is_valid_goa_account` as follows to make it work:
```
    private bool is_valid_goa_account(Goa.Object handle) {
        Goa.Mail? mail = handle.get_mail();
        return (
            mail != null &&
            !handle.get_account().mail_disabled &&
            ((!Geary.String.is_empty(mail.imap_host) &&
              !Geary.String.is_empty(mail.smtp_host)) ||
             handle.get_account().provider_type == "exchange")
        );
    }
```
But I think this is just a hack and should be reverted. I'm happy to share my changes of course. Can I push my own branch here? I'm not an expert of Gitlab.

@mcrha thanks for pitching in. That's excatly the kind of information I was looking for. So essentially it doesn't make sense to implement EWS autodiscovery if we want to stick to IMAP/SMTP. 

I propose to simply wrap the GOA account and try to connect to IMAP/SMTP using the Exchange server address (in my case I had to provide `outlook.office365.com` anyway to GOA).
If this fails then let the user configure the account manually, or disable it. Sounds reasonable?

